Question 13: The company wants to provide a promotional offer in the advertisement of the restaurants. The condition to get the offer is that the restaurants must have a rating count of more than 50 and the average rating should be greater than 4. Find the restaurants fulfilling the criteria to get the promotional offer. [3 marks]¶

In [ ]:
df_rated = df[df['rating'] != 'Not given'].copy()
# Convert rating column from object to integer
df_rated['rating'] = df_rated['rating'].astype('int')
df_rat_cnt = df_rated.groupby(['restaurant_name'])['rating'].count().sort_values(ascending = False).reset_index()
df_rat_cnt_50 = df_rat_cnt[df_rat_cnt['rating']>50]
rest_names = df_rat_cnt_50.groupby(['restaurant_name'])['rating'].mean()>4
rest_names.reset_index()

Observations: Only 4 restaurants 'Blue Ribbon Fried Chicken', 'Blue Ribbbon Sushi', 'Shake Shack' and 'The Meatball Shop' meet the above criteria of have a rating count of more than 50 and the average rating greater than 4.¶

Question 14: The company charges the restaurant 25% on the orders having cost greater than 20 dollars and 15% on the orders having cost greater than 5 dollars. Find the net revenue generated by the company across all orders. [3 marks]¶

In [ ]:
df['revenue'] = [i*0.25 if i > 20 else i*0.15 if i > 5 else i *0 for i in df.cost_of_the_order]
total_rev = df['revenue'].sum()
print('The net revenue is around',round(total_rev,2), 'dollars')

The net revenue is around 6166.3 dollars

Observations: The reveue is generated more when order costs more than 20$.¶

Question 16: The company wants to analyze the delivery time of the orders on weekdays and weekends. How does the mean delivery time vary during weekdays and weekends? [2 marks]¶

In [ ]:
df_day_weekend = df[df['day_of_the_week'] =='Weekend'].copy()
print('The mean delivery time during weekend',round(df_day_weekend['delivery_time'].mean(),2),'mins')
df_day_weekday = df[df['day_of_the_week'] =='Weekday'].copy()
print('The mean delivery time during weekday',round(df_day_weekday['delivery_time'].mean(),2),'mins')

The mean delivery time during weekend 22.47 mins
The mean delivery time during weekday 28.34 mins

Observations:¶

The mean delivery time during weekday is more as compared to mean delivery time on weekend. This could be due to various factors like traffic during weekdays, availability of more staff on weekends.

Conclusion and Recommendations¶

Question 17: What are your conclusions from the analysis? What recommendations would you like to share to help improve the business? (You can use cuisine type and feedback ratings to drive your business recommendations.) [6 marks]¶

Conclusions:¶

More than double of the orders are placed on weekends as compared to weekdays and thus maximum revenue is generated on weekend.

Most of the orders are not rated by the customers.

The most popular cuisines among customers are American,Japanese and Italian.

Average delivery time taken to deliver orders is around 24% and around 10% orders took more than hour to deliver.

The average delivery time during weekend is less than average delivery time during weekdays.

The higher revenue is generated from the orders which costs more than 20$.

Recommendations:¶

Need to encourage customers to rate their orders which will help us to improve our service.

Around 10% of orders took delivery time of more than 1 hour. This needs to be investigated further and improvements can be done.

Promotional offers like discount, loyaty points to be awarded to the customer who orders frequently.

More collaboration needs to be done with restaturants serving American, Japanese and Italian cuisines.
